olive oil
1 leek
½ apple
1 packet orecchiette
1 packet diced bacon
1 packet garlic paste
½ bottle cream
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle red wine vinegar
½ sachet Italian Herbs
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves

• Half-fill a large saucepan with water, add a generous pinch of salt, then bring
to the boil over high heat.
• Cook orecchiette in boiling water until ‘al dente’, 8 minutes.
• Reserve some pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people), then
drain orecchiette and set aside.

TIP: 'Al dente' pasta is cooked through but still slightly firm in the centre.

Little cooks: Older kids can help add the pasta to the saucepan under adult
supervision. Be careful, the water is boiling!

• When the pasta has 5 minutes cook time remaining, thinly slice leek.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add leek and cook until softened, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic paste and Italian herbs (see ingredients) and cook until fragrant,
1 minute.

• Add cream (see ingredients) to the frying pan and cook, stirring, 30 seconds.
• Add cooked orecchiette, some reserved pasta water (1/4 cup for 2 people
/ 1/2 cup for 4 people), the grated Parmesan cheese and baby spinach
leaves and cook, stirring, until just wilted, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.
• Thinly slice apple (see ingredients).

TIP: Add another splash of reserved pasta water if the sauce looks too thick.

• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, apple and a drizzle of red
wine vinegar and olive oil. Toss to combine and season.
• Divide bacon and leek orecchiette between bowls.
• Serve with apple salad. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Take the lead by tossing the salad!